<H1>NC Writer Online Help</H1></A> 
<P>Welcome to NC Writer help.  This document contains information about the following topics:

<P><A HREF="#intro">Introduction</A>: Provides a brief overview of the word processor.
<P><A HREF="#Procedures">Procedures</A>: Describes how to edit text, change fonts, save documents, print, and quit the application.
<P><A HREF="#Toolbar">Using the Toolbar</A>: Describes the word processor toolbar functions.
<P><A HREF="#Keyboard">Using the Keyboard</A>: Describes the word processor keyboard shortcuts.
<P><A HREF="ncfrescointernal:cancel">Return to Word Processor </A>: Closes this help page and returns you to the Word Processor.

<P><H2><A NAME="intro">Introduction</A></H2>
<P>The word processor is an easy-to-use application built in to the Network Computer. You can use the Word Processor to write letters, memos, reports and other documents. Documents can be saved for future reference or printed to obtain a hard copy. Additionally, you can move and copy text from one document to another and from a Web page to a word processor document.<P>

