<A HREF="ncfrescointernal:cancel">[Return to Word Processor]</A><BR><HR>

<A NAME="Procedures"><H2>Procedures</H2></A>
<P>This section covers the following topics:

<P><A HREF="#PROC1">Moving the Caret</A>
<P><A HREF="#PROC2">Editing Text</A>
<P><A HREF="#PROC3">Changing the Font</A>
<P><A HREF="#PROC4">Saving Documents</A>
<P><A HREF="#PROC5">Printing</A>
<P><A HREF="#PROC6">Quitting the Application</A>

<P><H3><A NAME="PROC1">Moving the Caret</A></H3> 
The caret is the little (red) 'I-beam' which indicates where text is typed. In a blank document, the caret appears in the top left corner. When you have typed in some text, you can move the caret around the page.
<P> The caret can be moved around the document by either moving the mouse pointer around the screen and pressing the mouse button or using the cursor keys.

<P><H3><A NAME="PROC2">Editing Text</A></H3> 
Editing text means cutting, copying and pasting text. Before you carry out any of these actions, you must first select the text to be edited.
<P> Move the mouse pointer to where you want the selection to begin - at the start of a word or paragraph, for example. Press the mouse button then drag the selection as far as you want it to go. Alternatively, use the cursor keys to move the caret to where you want the selection to begin. Then press the <B>Menu</B> button and choose <B>Edit -&gt; Start selection</B>. Use the arrow buttons again to move the caret to the end of the selection.

<H4>Moving Text</H4> 
<OL><LI>Select the text you want to move. 
<LI>Click on the <IMG WIDTH=25 HEIGHT=25 SRC="icontype:nc_vcut"> button.
<LI>Move the caret where you want to move the selection to.
<LI>Click on the <IMG WIDTH=25 HEIGHT=25 SRC="icontype:nc_vpast"> button.</OL>
The text you selected to move is inserted at the caret. 

<H4>Copying Text</H4> 
<OL><LI>Select the text you want to copy.
<LI>Click on the <IMG WIDTH=25 HEIGHT=25 SRC="icontype:nc_vcopy"> button.
<LI>Move the caret where you want to copy the selection to.
<LI>Click on the <IMG WIDTH=25 HEIGHT=25 SRC="icontype:nc_vpast"> button.</OL> 
The text you selected to copy is inserted at the caret. 

<P><H3><A NAME="PROC3">Changing the Font</A></H3> 
The Font refers to the appearance and size of the text characters you use in a document. 
<P> You can set the following text attributes for any text selection: 
<UL> 
<LI><B>Font</B>: the typeface, i.e. Trinity, Homerton etc.
<LI><B>Font size</B>: the size of the typeface measured in points (1/72&quot;).
<LI><B>Font color</B>: the foreground color used for the font. 
<LI><B>Font style</B>: the look of the font i.e. Italic, Bold or Underline, or more than one of these characteristics at once.
</UL> 

<P>Use the following steps to change the appearance of the text:
<OL><LI>Select the part of the document you want to change retrospectively.
<LI>Click on <IMG WIDTH=25 HEIGHT=25 SRC="icontype:nc_vmenu"> to display the menu. 
<LI>Choose the <B>Font</B> you want, the <B>Font size</B>, the <B>Font color</B> and the <B>Font style</B>. (You can also choose Font style from the button bar.)</OL>

<P><H3><A NAME="PROC4">Saving Documents</A></H3>
To save the current document displayed, click on the <IMG WIDTH=25 HEIGHT=25 SRC="icontype:nc_vsave"> button.

<P>Use the following steps if you would like to save the current document with a different name:
<OL><LI>Click on <IMG WIDTH=25 HEIGHT=25 SRC="icontype:nc_vmenu"> to display the menu. 
<LI>Select the <B>Document -&gt;  Title -&gt; </B> menu item.
<LI>Enter a new document title and press Enter.
<LI>Click on the <IMG WIDTH=25 HEIGHT=25 SRC="icontype:nc_vsave"> button.</OL>
The current document is saved with the new name.

<P><H3><A NAME="PROC5">Printing</A></H3> 
To print the current document displayed in the word processor, click on the <IMG WIDTH=25 HEIGHT=25 SRC="icontype:nc_vprnt"> button.

<P><B>Note:</B> Use the following steps if you are using a television monitor with your NC.
<OL><LI>Click on <IMG WIDTH=25 HEIGHT=25 SRC="icontype:nc_vmenu"> to display the menu. 
<LI>Select the <B>Document -&gt; Print</B> menu item.</OL> 
The current document is printed.

<P><H3><A NAME="PROC6">Quitting the Application</A></H3>
You can exit the word processor at any time by clicking on the <IMG WIDTH=25 HEIGHT=25 SRC="icontype:nc_vclos"> button.</OL>
<P>The word processor quits and you are returned to your starting point.<P>

